'''Nijūgoyū''' (二十五有) refers to the classification of the [[:en:Sentient beings (Buddhism)|sentient beings]] and their existence in the {{ill|cycle of birth and death|ja|生死|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/cycle of birth and death|qq=}} (shōji) into twenty-five types.
The breakdown of this classification consists of twenty-five categories: the Four Continents ({{ill|Four Continents|ja|四洲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Four Continents|qq=}}, shiyū), {{ill|Four Evil Realms|ja|四悪趣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Four Evil Realms|qq=}} (shiakushu), {{ill|Six Desire Heavens|ja|六欲天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Six Desire Heavens|qq=}} (roku yokuten), [[:en:Brahmā (Buddhism)|Brahma Heavens]] (bonten, one type), Non-perception Heaven ({{ill|Non-perception Heaven|ja|無想天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Non-perception Heaven|qq=}}, musōten, one type), Five Pure Abodes ({{ill|Five Pure Abodes|ja|五那含天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Five Pure Abodes|qq=}} or {{ill|Five Pure Abodes|ja|五浄居天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Five Pure Abodes|qq=}}, gojōgoten, one type), Four Meditation Heavens ({{ill|Four Meditation Heavens|ja|四禅天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Four Meditation Heavens|qq=}}, shizen-ten, four types), and Four Formless Heavens ({{ill|Four Formless Heavens|ja|四空処天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Four Formless Heavens|qq=}}, shikūshoten, four types).<ref name="koko-do">Buddhist Dictionary (edited by Kōkōdō), p.998</ref><ref>[http://jodoshuzensho.jp/daijiten/index.php/%E4%BA%8C%E5%8D%81%E4%BA%94%E6%9C%89 Web Edition: New Compilation Jōdo Sect Great Dictionary/Nijūgoyū]</ref>
The term "Yū" (有) signifies "the persistence of cause and effect," indicating that causes inevitably lead to results.<ref name="koko-do" />
